Representative Blust
1 moves to amend the bill on page 1, line 3, by inserting the following language before the period:
2 "AND PREVENTING A REDUCTION IN PUBLIC SERVICE COMPANY VALUES FOR
3 COUNTIES SUBJECT TO THE MORATORIUM";
4
5 and on page 2, line 14, by rewriting that line to read:
6 "SECTION 1.5.(a) This section applies only to public service company system
7 property that is located in a county subject to the property tax reappraisal moratorium under
8 Section 1 of this act.
9 SECTION 1.5.(b) Property described in subsection (a) of this section is designated
10 a special class of property under Article V, Sec. 2(2) of the North Carolina Constitution and shall
11 be assessed for taxation in accordance with this section. G.S. 105-284(b) is repealed.
12 SECTION 1.5.(c) This section is effective for taxes imposed for taxable years
13 beginning on or after July 1, 2026, and expires for taxes imposed for taxable years beginning on
14 or after July 1, 2027.
15 SECTION 2. Except as otherwise provided, this act is effective when it becomes
16 law.".
